# Icon chips (Settings, Profile, Home stats, Budget)

## Required pattern

Use **`AppIconChip`** or **`uiIconChipStyle(accentColor, isDark, lightBg?)`** from `src/app/theme/darkModeUi.ts` for every small UI icon in a rounded square (settings rows, profile fields, home stat strip, currency picker, notifications, data export, etc.).

```tsx
import { AppIconChip } from '../ui/AppIconChip';

<AppIconChip icon={ChartBar} accentColor="#EF4444" lightBg="#FEE2E2" />
```

## Light mode

- Container uses a **pastel background** — pass explicit `lightBg` (e.g. `#EDEDFF`, `#D1FAE5`) or rely on `hexToRgba(accentColor, 0.14)`.
- Icon glyph uses the **accent color** directly.

## Dark mode

- Container uses **`onboardingIconGradient(accentColor)`** (dark accent gradient, same as Budget & Goals feature cards).
- Icon glyph is **white / `#FFFFFF`** (`ONBOARDING_CHIP_ICON`).

## Category icons

Use **`CategoryIcon`** with default `tone="auto"` — pastel `category.bg` in light mode, gradient dark.

**Exception:** Settings category **pills** use `tone="light"` — no chip background inside the pill (icon only).

## Feature cards

Use **`FeatureCardIcon`** / **`featureIconTile`** — light mode uses `accentBg` pastel tile + accent glyph; dark mode uses gradient + white glyph.

## Do not

- Leave icon containers transparent in light mode on main app screens.
- Use dark tinted surfaces (`mixTowardBlack`) for light-mode feature card icons.

## Chart tooltips

Use **`chartTooltipStyle()`** — dark background `#14141E`, light label/value text. Never `c.text` as tooltip bg in dark mode.

## Active pills (List / Insights toggle, Month / Year)

When the active tab has a **light** background in dark mode (`tabActiveBg`), foreground must be **`tabActiveIcon`** (dark ink), not `onAccent`.
